          <p>Liverpool has one of the highest concentrations of Victorian and Edwardian housing in England. These properties present specific challenges for central heating installation: solid walls that require surface-mounted pipework or careful channelling, chimneys used as flue routes that may need lining, cellar entries that affect pipework routing and original features that need to be preserved. Our engineers have 30 years experience navigating these challenges across Liverpool's terraced streets. The <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/domestic/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HSE gas safety standards</a> apply regardless of property age and we bring every installation up to current regulations.</p>
          <h3 style="color:var(--navy);font-size:1rem;margin:0.75rem 0 0.4rem;text-align:center;">How do I know what size boiler I need for my Liverpool home?</h3>
          <p>Boiler sizing depends on the number of radiators, property size, number of bathrooms and insulation levels. Our engineers carry out a full heat loss calculation at the free survey to ensure the boiler is correctly sized. An oversized boiler short-cycles, reducing efficiency and warranty life. An undersized boiler struggles to maintain temperature on cold Liverpool days. Getting the sizing right from the start is one of the most important decisions in a central heating installation.</p>
