          <p>A sludge-filled central heating system can reduce boiler efficiency by 15 to 25%. On a typical Liverpool household spending £900 per year on gas heating, that represents a saving of £135 to £225 per year after a power flush costing £350. In many cases the power flush pays for itself within two years through reduced energy bills alone. The <a href="https://energysavingtrust.org.uk/advice/thermostats-and-heating-controls/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Energy Saving Trust</a> recommends regular system maintenance as a key energy-saving measure.</p>
